Ron also pioneered some .40 caliber rifles for all types of black powder shooting; the 40/60 and 40/65 being two of his favorites. 

We are pleased to offer an outstanding Ron Long Winchester High Wall. Ron didn’t trade mark very many of his custom rifles, but this is one of the rare few that he did. 

Chambered in his own .40-60 Long, the barrel is a straight-octagon configuration 30 inches in length and 1.250 inches across the flats. This handsome custom rifle weighs in at 13 pounds and the barrel is complimented with three Unertl scope bases.

There is a mar to the checkering at the top point of the left grip panel. There is also a chip in the finish on the lower right side of the buttstock, with very minor handling marks on the barrel.

The action is a coil-spring Winchester High Wall and is fitted with close-coupled set triggers. While the receiver is blued, the lever wears the beautiful colors of traditional casehardening.

Nikon Monarch 8-32X50ED SF Riflescopes are perfect for extreme long range hunting and target shooting. Like all Monarchs the three new riflescopes were developed to give shooters increased versatility and superlative performance with virtually any type of rifle, in any caliber and in any imaginable hunting situation. The Nikon 8-32X50ED SF is the first rifle scope to incorporate Nikon's exclusive and legendary ED glass. Nikon ED glass delivers superior sharpness and color correction for unmatched detail resolution. While still maintaining the American-preferred one-inch diameter main body tube, Monarch Riflescopes where developed to not only provide the shooter with a big, bright, sharp sight picture, but at the same time minimize the overall length of the scope-and maximize the mount ringspacing capability.
